The local unit was little swayed by the domestic CPI release, whipsawing throughout the day, with eyes turned towards today’s Jackson Hole retreat to gauge the direction of US monetary policy. At the close of local trade, the rand quoted 0.48% weaker at R16.90/$, after trading in range of R16.76/$ - R16.92/$. The rand managed to recoup some of yesterday’s losses overnight. July PPI inflation data is due for release today, but most of the direction is likely to come from the US dollar. Expected range today R16.75/$ - R17.00/$. South African bourse The JSE All Share (+0.82%) ended higher yesterday, led by gains in large gold (+3.98%) and technology (+2.34%) stocks. In local news, Nedbank reported a drop in half-year profits of close to 70% yesterday, saying it hopes the worst impact of Covid-19 is over. However, traders were less convinced as the bank’s stock price tumbled by 5.68%. In the overall emerging market sphere, the MSCI Emerging Market Index (+0.41 percent) traded firmer. --IOL--